data.description: This spacious and newly constructed ranch style home for sale is located at the end of Perrin Street in Ravenden, Arkansas. This home sits on more than 2 acres on a dead-end street with very little neighbors and woods around the property. Plenty of room to roam with some of the land being partially fenced and a concrete slab for a future shop building if needed. The home itself has a beautiful, covered porch around two sides and wide enough for outside furniture. Inside the 1800 square foot rustic and ranch style home, you will find 3 bedrooms with 2 1/2 Baths. The interior is lined with pinewood walls throughout and rustic metal ceilings. The open floor plan is very nice with plenty of living room space that flows into the kitchen. Enough room for a huge dining table with room to spare. This home allows someone to add their own decorating style while having the natural wood and rustic feeling in every room. When you leave the huge utility room, you enter the 600 square foot insulated garage that is currently used as a woodworking shop and extra bonus room. This room would also make an excellent den or huge game room. For heating and cooling, a 5 head mini-split system is the main source with a gas fireplace in the living room. Poured concrete flooring throughout with metal siding and roof, this home is very easy to maintain and with the spray foam insulation, very practical as well. This home was completed in 2022 and located not far from the scenic Spring River and the public access being just a few miles from this property. A few miles away, you will find the Historic town of Hardy, Arkansas with shopping and restaurants along with the Harold E. Alexander Wildlife Management Area with over 12,000 acres of public hunting in close proximity to this homestead. Kitchen appliances to convey.
